    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-25T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-25T10:00:00-05:00" n="374"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Czechoslovakia/175: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia (<persName type="from"
                            >Ratshesky</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-25T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 25, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 25—12:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Department’s telegram No. 15, April 23, 1 p.m. At conference this morning
                    with Dr. <persName corresp="#p_KK1">Krofta</persName>, Acting Minister of
                    Foreign Affairs, I was informed that Dr. <persName corresp="#p_BE2"
                        >Beneš</persName> who is at Geneva has today designated the Czechoslovak
                    Minister at Washington<note n="22" xml:id="d374fn22">
                        <persName corresp="#p_VF1">Ferdinand Veverka</persName>.</note> as the
                    representative of Czechoslovakia to conduct the necessary negotiations. He is
                    being advised by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ratshesky</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
